          "description": "This time I visited Bellevue hospital because I needed to make sure how I was doing with ITU symptoms. I finished my 2nd treatment and days later I was uncomfortable. Taking good advantage my son went to see his dad, after few trips back and forth I was able to show up. After I was seeing by doctor then nurse, it was okay,  that nurse was a male named Marco in E.R., he's \ud83d\udc4d good!. After 2 hours I was starving and feeling dizzy. I asked a volunteer guy for a vending machine,  instead he offered me some foods, Another nurse refused that offer, then nurse Marco came in with kindness gave me a sandwich \ud83e\udd6a, .\n\nDiabetes patients should be treated kindly,  all patients deserve it but Diabetes patients are more delicated. 1st and 2nd doctors I saw, they were good \ud83d\udc4d. But that nurse who refused to assist me, God have mercy on him, people are heart hardened and heartless.\n\nNow for that nurse Marco, I wish all blessings \ud83d\ude4c \ud83d\ude4f \u2764\ufe0f , now and always. He should be head of all nurses. His performance was outstanding, it was great,  it was excellent, it was good \ud83d\udc4d \ud83d\udc4f.",
