        {
          "username": "Florence Graydon",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "104515137960518787925",
          "user_review_count": 4,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTs8x18Ez9KjzTOUuEXsETJMlNX9FQuKXZ_K3ZkTbdzGdlSFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "My experience was excellent from the emergency room to the Stroke Center to Rehab.  I was extremely afraid having suffered a Stroke.  I was transported from Queens Hospital to Bellevue.  I was to have emergency surgery. Bellevue staff was waiting for me . Underwent another CT and MRI.  After both it was determined surgery was not necessary at this time.  I was treated medically with anticoagolents and admitted to the Stroke Center on the 16th floor.  While there I underwent many tests and continued being treated wuth anticoagolents.They gradually added my meds including my blood thinner.  The resident and Care doctors saw me each morning.  The Care Team saw me every morning for 5 days. At the end of 5 days I was transferred to Acute Rehab pn the 6th floor.  In Rehab I received intensive OT and PT for 3 hours a day.  The therapist were excellent.  I remained in Rehab for some 10 days.  I was discharged May 15th home.  My care on Rehab was excellent - Nurses  PCAs, meal servers, doctors were all responsive, respectful and showed they cared about the patients.  The PT and OT gym and facility included everything needed.  I commend the therapist for their expertise,, professionalism  and overall caring.  I would recommend this Rehab very highly.  Upon discharge I felt ready to go home.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT201TlpYTnljVmhKYVVGTWNXWjNhVjlTTVRWblpuYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x67a293dafcc5f7e0!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOm5NZXNycVhJaUFMcWZ3aV9SMTVnZnc%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "4 weeks ago",
