        },
        {
          "username": "Noneof Yourbusiness",
          "rating": 4,
          "contributor_id": "109930713817142539457",
          "user_review_count": 2,
          "user_photo_count": 1,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqOkBRiWcm6lN8h3ddOaojINQvIs61a2xtzHfmX7pPmUUgWA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "My partner suffered a massive stroke a month ago and was brought to Bellevue ICU neuro dept . That department saved his life . I am forever grateful and was thoroughly impressed with staff attending to him there . I also like that visiting hours on that floor is 24/7. Then he was moved to a stroke floor was there for about 2 weeks but I really didn\u2019t like the vibe there . Then he was moved to the 6th floor physical therapy and all the PCA\u2019s were so attentive and caring to his needs .  I felt confident with him being there . I can\u2019t remember all their names but Segura was wonderful !! Excellent bedside manner . My only issue is the PT team working with him thought it be best for him to be transferred to a sub acute nursing home because he wasn\u2019t interacting with them during PT . He just had a stroke he\u2019s not 100% and I felt they just gave up on him too quickly.  That really bothered me . The only reason I gave 4 stars  is because as mentioned Bellevue saved his life and the PCA\u2019s God bless them all . They were the best!",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pWRmEybERObTgwTldGMWJtdHVZWEJ6UWtSemFtYxAB!2m1!1s0x0:0x67a293dafcc5f7e0!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOjVFa2lDNm80NWF1bmtuYXBzQkRzamc%7C%7C?hl=en",
